data.title: Australian Honours and Awards
data.meta_site_name: Governor of New South Wales. Her Excellency the Honourable Margaret Beazley AC KC
data.text:
Australia has a system of honours and awards to recognise Australians for excellence, achievement and meritorious service. These awards were introduced on 14 February 1975.

The Governor conducts investiture ceremonies twice a year at Government House Sydney for New South Wales recipients of Australian Honours and Awards. Recipients are announced on Australia Day and on the Kingâ€™s Birthday.
